title: mini-THON kickoff at Governor Mifflin
description: Tim Hartung. a 2010 Governor Mifflin graduate and cancer survivor. provided some motivating words to students during a mini-THON kickoff rally on Jan. 14. Hartung founded the mini-THON at the school which raises money for the Four Diamonds Fund at Penn State Hershey Children's Hospital. The mini-THON will be held in March. Students can dance. swim and play games during mini-THON.

title: Campus Jr High Class of 1956 Reunion
description: The class of 1956 from the Campus Junior High School returned to the Kutztown University campus for a reunion on Jan. 6. The junior high school closed down after their class graduated in 1956.

Dr. Chovanes' opening statement at forum
description: During a recent open forum. Surgeon Dr. George Chovanes gives his opening statement explaining why he wants to be the state senator for District 11. On Jan. 22. The Berks County Republican Committee's Executive Board will choose the candidate to run against the Democratic candidate in the special election on March 15.

title: Michael Rivera says why he wants to be a senator
description: Michael Rivera. assistant vice president. Small Business Services for the Greater Reading Area Chamber of Commerce. discusses the reasons why he would make a good candidate for state senator. He was one of six candidates at a recent forum hosted by the Berks County Republican Committee at Exeter Junior High School.

title: James Smith shares why he wants to be senator
description: Attorney James M. Smith shares why he wants to be state senator during a candidate forum hosted by the Berks County Republican Committee in Exeter.

title: Barry Jozwiak shares opening statement
description: Former Berks County sheriff Barry J. Jozwiak shares why he is a good candidate for state senator. He was one of six that spoke at a recent Republican forum.

description: Register Larry Medaglia shares his opening statement at a recent candidates forum in Exeter.

title: Kenneth A. Smith says why he wants to be a senator
description: Exeter Supervisor Kenneth A. Smith talks about why he wants to be a state senator.

title: Kutztown Police receive life-saving devices
description: The Friends of Reading Hospital donated five AEDs to the Kutztown Police Department recently. Kutztown now has an AED in every marked and unmarked police vehicle.

title: Teachers Assoc.: We're not greedy
description: The Kutztown Area Teachers' Association speaks to the school board on Monday night about the fact that they are working without a contract.

title: Kutztown School Board recognized
description: Kutztown Superintendent Nicholas Lazo Jr. recognized the school board on Monday night.

title: Sledding in Exeter Township
description: Exeter students enjoyed the winter weather by sledding down the hill between the high school and junior high school after the storm brought about a foot to the area.
